th s1 (概要), I need to pull the class name and basic description from the source material. I'm documenting the HttpAccessLogHandler class, which outputs HTTP access logs for both inbound and outbound requests, and noting that it needs to be positioned after ThreadContextHandler since it relies on context items that handler sets up, while HttpErrorHandler should come after it to handle exceptions that aren't already converted to HTTP responses.\n\nNow I'm outlining the handler's processing flow: on the inbound path it logs the HTTP request and execution context at INFO level, then delegates to subsequent handlers; on the return path it logs the complete request, context, and response information.\n\nFor exception handling, if an HTTP error response occurs, I log the error details along with the request and context before re-throwing; for other exceptions, I log the request and context information and then re-throw as well.\n\nThis handler has no configuration options itself—the logger configuration is documented separately. I'm setting up the component definition with the HttpAccessLogHandler class. Since there are no Javadoc URLs to collect and the base URL is empty, the official_doc_urls array will be empty. Now I'm assembling the final JSON output with all the collected information.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18112,"cache_read_input_tokens":18643,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18112,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ccbd481e-c0e8-48fc-a679-5b5a4f0e9a0c","uuid":"22a31672-d10b-41da-a9f8-4834614c0e6e"}
